post.summary: Insert matrix data into PostgreSQL database and matrix metadata into a device.
post.description:
Splits data and metadata resulting from build endpoint. Works only with MGRS data. Requires access token.  
Before inserting data, ownership of the device metadata is checked (by id, contexbroker and organization), if exists. Otherwise is created.

requestBody.description: Requires an appropriate JSON Object of the data. Date accepted are in YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS format or ISO string format. Preferrable ISO string format.

example.description: people walking from origin to destination

200.description: Successful operation. Return an object {message, status} and 200 status.

400.description: Missing parameter in data or url inserted. Return an object {message, status} and 400 status.

409.description: No ownership on that device. Return an object {message, status} and 409 status.

example.message:
registration is possible the model ODMModel is NOT of type authenticated Problem in inserting the device ABCDE_Organization_1000 in the database. :
Duplicate entry no URI has been generated by the KB no registration in the context broker

get.description:
Retrieve matrix data from PostgreSQL database. Works only with MGRS data. Requires access token.
Before retriving data, ownership of the device metadata is checked (by id, contexbroker and organization), if exists.

parameters.name: precision
parameters.description:
Cell dimension according to the MGRS standard, measured in meters.  
Possible values are 1, 10, 100, 1000, 10000, 100000.

parameters.name: from_date
parameters.description: Start date of measurements. Date accepted are in YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS format or ISO string format. Preferrable ISO string format.

parameters.name: inflow
parameters.description: Boolean value to get the incoming (true) or outgoing (false) flow.

200.description: Successful operation. Returns a Feature Collection object and 200 status.

400.description: Missing paramter in the query. The key of message object is the missed parameter.

message.longitude: Missing required parameter in the JSON body or the post body or the query string

get.description:
Retrieve matrix data from PostgreSQL database. Works only with GADM and ISTAT data. Requires access token.  
Before inserting data, ownership of the device metadata is checked (by id, contexbroker and organization), if exists.

parameters.name: precision
parameters.description:
Cell dimension according to the MGRS standard, measured in meters.  
Possible values are 1, 10, 100, 1000, 10000, 100000.

parameters.name: from_date
parameters.description: Start date of measurements. Date accepted are in YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS format or ISO string format. Preferrable ISO string format.

parameters.name: inflow
parameters.description: Boolean value to get the incoming (true) or outgoing (false) flow.

parameters.name: od_id
parameters.description: Id of origin destination matrix. Must be GADM or ISTAT device.

parameters.name: source
parameters.description: Name of the database source. Required only if the searched data is ISTAT type.

200.description: Successful operation. Returns a Feature Collection object and 200 status.

400.description: Missing paramter in the query. The key of message object is the missed parameter.

message.longitude: Missing required parameter in the JSON body or the post body or the query string
